<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-3413] Log4j2 Incorrectly Uses System Property For Level Setting And Got IllegalArgumentException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-3413</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have an environment parameter in IBM WAS 9 running JAVA 8 with a name of &quot;level&quot; and a value of &quot;DEVL&quot;.&#160; This parameter is used by applications to detect the environment they are on and worked fine with log4j2.8.2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After upgraded to Log4j2.17.1, for some reason the Log4j2 grabs that parameter during the initialization, ignoring the settings in the log4j2.xml, and spills a &lt;em&gt;java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Unknown level constant &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;DEVL&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&#160;in the system log.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;IBM WAS 9, JAVA 8&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="13430464">LOG4J2-3413</key>
